com.google.gwt.dev
Class PermutationWorkerFactory

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.dev.PermutationWorkerFactory
Direct Known Subclasses:
ExternalPermutationWorkerFactory, ThreadedPermutationWorkerFactory
public abstract class PermutationWorkerFactory
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a factory for implementations of an endpoint that will invoke CompilePerms. Implementations of PermutationWorkerFactory should be default-instantiable and will have init(com.google.gwt.core.ext.TreeLogger) called immediately after construction.

compilePermutations

public static void compilePermutations(TreeLogger logger,
                                       Precompilation precompilation,
                                       Permutation[] permutations,
                                       int localWorkers,
                                       java.util.List<FileBackedObject<PermutationResult>> resultFiles)
                                throws UnableToCompleteException
Compiles a subset of the Permutations in a Precompilation and returns an array of Files that can be consumed by Link using the system-default PermutationWorkersFactories.

Parameters:
localWorkers - Set the maximum number of workers that should be executed on the local system by the PermutationWorkerFactory. The value WORKERS_AUTO will allow the PermutationWorkerFactory to apply a heuristic to determine the correct number of local workers.
resultFiles - the output files to write into; must be the same length as permutations
Throws:
UnableToCompleteException
